headline: MOH Q1 Earnings Call: Revenue Beat Driven by Membership Growth, Guidance Reaffirmed Amid Rate and Cost Trends
summary: Healthcare insurance company Molina Healthcare (NYSE:MOH) reported Q1 CY2025 results beating Wall Street’s revenue expectations, with sales up 12.2% year on year to $11.15 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $6.08 per share was 2.1% above analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: 3 S&P 500 Stocks to Research Further
summary: The S&P 500 (^GSPC) is full of established businesses, but only some continue to outperform the market. A few standout companies are thriving thanks to strong fundamentals and sustained competitive advantages.
